# Groq API Key for Online transcription (recommended)
# Get your FREE API key from: https://console.groq.com
# Free tier: 14,400 seconds/day (4 hours of audio)
# Lightning fast: 0.3s to transcribe 60s of audio
# If not set, the app will use Offline mode (browser-based speech recognition)
VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your-api-key-here

# Google Drive API (Optional - for automatic cloud sync)
# Setup instructions: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 1. Create a new project
# 2. Enable Google Drive API
# 3. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Web application)
# 4. Add authorized origins: http://localhost:5173, your production URL
# 5. Add authorized redirect URIs: http://localhost:5173, your production URL
# 6. Copy the Client ID below
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_HERE

# Microsoft OneDrive API (Optional - for automatic cloud sync)
# Setup instructions: https://portal.azure.com/
# 1. Go to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
# 2. Create new registration
# 3. Supported accounts: "Personal Microsoft accounts"
# 4. Redirect URI: Web - http://localhost:5173, your production URL
# 5. Enable "Access tokens" in Authentication > Implicit grant
# 6. Add API permission: Microsoft Graph > Files.ReadWrite
# 7. Copy the Application (client) ID below
VITE_MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID_HERE
